comment: The way she's stumbling over her words, hesitating and repeating herself are clear signs of her making stuff up. As much as I hate to admit it, when in situations when I need to back pedal or lie about a story (typically to get me out of trouble with my parents) I do the exact same thing. When faced with confrontation that I'm not expecting I try to lie my way out of it or bend the truth and my speech sounds nearly identical to hers, which is why I never get away with it. As well, her repeating herself but changing the explanation slightly or changing her mind about the story are clear manipulation and gas lighting. I've had (and am still having although I now recognize it so it no longer works) someone use these tactics on me. They're effective in disorienting and confusing the person you're talking to, allowing you to manipulate the story into whatever you want it to be because the other person's recount becomes unreliable. "I don't remember hitting the door" "I didn't hit the door" "I may have hit the door but I don't remember" "I probably did it because of my toes" are all things she said about the door. She's a manipulator and it's so incredibly obvious.
